                     <interp inst="t18261207-255-person1407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I found this property on the prisoner at the watch-house - I compared it with what remains at the building - it fits exactly - it is a water-pipe, and was fixed to the cistern.</p>
               <p>GEORGE CROWHURST. These three chisels are mine, and were on Messrs. Harding's premises.</p>
               <p>JAMES HARDING, JUN. This building was in the Circus, facing the London Institution - it is in the City - it belongs to my father only - I am in partnership with him, but not in this building; I have seen the pipe fitted with what remains - it fits exactly.</p>
